<title>ARGENTINA: Salomon changes Latin portfolio weightings.</title>
<headline>Salomon changes Latin portfolio weightings.</headline>
<dateline>BUENOS AIRES 1997-01-27</dateline>
<text>
<p>Salomon Brothers Inc. said Monday it has reduced Chile, Argentina, Mexico and Peru in its recommended country portfolio weighting for Latin America.</p>
<p>At the same time, the weightings of Colombia, Venezuela and Brazil were raised, Salomon said in a statement.  </p>
<p>Salomon said its new portfolio is overweight on cyclical sectors in Mexico and Argentina and Brazil's state-owned sectors.</p>
<p>Although Argentina's weighting was reduced, the country remains modestly overweight. &quot;Brazilian equities are overweighted largely due to attractive valuation ratios and despite a mixed macro-political outlook,&quot; said Salomon.</p>
<p>Colombia and Venezuela &quot;are overweighted due to low valuation multiples and low Betas,&quot; added Salomon's.</p>
<p>Chile's stocks are underweighted largely because of expensive valuations.</p>
<p>((--Axel Bugge, Buenos Aires Newsroom, 541 318-0668))</p>
